                    "company": "Rabobank",
                    "description": "The Programme Office supports the Management Team COO WRR (Wholesale, Rural & Retail) on several priorities, such as the setup of WRR value chains to manage the IT project portfolio, alignment of the global Service center to WRR business (SLA management, Performance Management) and Benefit Management. Thereby aligning the mission, vision and strategy of Rabobank WRR and the COO domain with the current change projects. These projects, its complexity and changes related to the organization suit my background (master Change Management).\n\nOne of my roles is Benefit Analyst for Benefit Management. I help implementing this new discipline within WRR. With Benefit Management we aim to redeem Benefits as promised in business cases. That seems logical, however was never done in the past. It creates awareness and helps the organization focusing on Benefits. The Benefit Analyst creates the benefit map for the organization and analyses progress of benefit realization.\n\nMy second role is that of Global Reporting on the project portfolio for COO WRR. I collect delivery status updates of the global portfolio from all international regions of Rabobank and combine it to meaningful management information.",
